<section class="section" id="quickstart">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Quickstart</h2>

    <h3>Docker Compose (recommended)</h3>
    <pre class="code"><code>git clone https://github.com/cubicecho/mcp-router mcp-router &amp;&amp; cd mcp-router
cp .env.example .env      <span class="cmt"># set a real MCP_ROUTER_TOKEN</span>
docker compose up -d</code></pre>
    <p>Open <code>http://localhost:3000</code>, enter your token, and install servers from the Browse page. All
      state lives in <code>./data</code>, bind-mounted to <code>/data</code> in the container.</p>

    <h3>Bare Node <span class="pill">Node ≥ 22.18</span></h3>
    <pre class="code"><code>npm install
npm run build
MCP_ROUTER_TOKEN=your-secret-token npm start</code></pre>
    <p>Listens on port 3000 (override with <code>PORT</code>) and serves the built web UI. If you start without a
      token, one is generated into <code>data/config/settings.json</code> and logged once.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Connect a client</h2>
    <p>Point <strong>Claude Code</strong> at the aggregate endpoint — every enabled server, tools named
      <code>&lt;server&gt;__&lt;tool&gt;</code>:</p>
    <pre class="code"><code>claude mcp add --transport http router http://localhost:3000/mcp \
  --header "Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;"</code></pre>

    <p>Or expose a single server, un-namespaced:</p>
    <pre class="code"><code>claude mcp add --transport http github http://localhost:3000/mcp/github \
  --header "Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;"</code></pre>

    <p>Or a <strong>project</strong> — a custom aggregate of just the servers that client should see:</p>
    <pre class="code"><code>claude mcp add --transport http coding http://localhost:3000/mcp/p/coding-assistant \
  --header "Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;"</code></pre>

    <p>Any client that speaks streamable HTTP works with the usual JSON config:</p>
    <pre class="code"><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "router": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "http://localhost:3000/mcp",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer &lt;token&gt;" }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

